    • Class com.netflix.genie.common.model.JobInfoElement extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • jobID

          java.lang.String jobID
          User given or system generated unique job id.

        • jobName

          java.lang.String jobName
          User given or system generated job name .

        • description

          java.lang.String description
          human readable description.

        • userName

          java.lang.String userName
          User who submitted the job.

        • groupName

          java.lang.String groupName
          The group user belongs.

        • userAgent

          java.lang.String userAgent
          Source System - UC4, Ab Initio, Search.

        • jobType

          java.lang.String jobType
          Job type - hadoop, pig and hive (upper case in DB).

        • clusterName

          java.lang.String clusterName
          Alias - Cluster Name.

        • clusterId

          java.lang.String clusterId
          ID for the cluster that is running the job.

        • schedule

          java.lang.String schedule
          Schedule type - adhoc or sla (upper case in DB).

        • configuration

          java.lang.String configuration
          Configuration - prod, test, unittest (upper case in DB).

        • cmdArgs

          java.lang.String cmdArgs
          Command line arguments.

        • fileDependencies

          java.lang.String fileDependencies
          File dependencies.

        • attachments

          FileAttachment[] attachments
          Set of file dependencies, sent as MIME attachments. This is not persisted in the DB for space reasons.

        • archiveLocation

          java.lang.String archiveLocation
          Location of logs being archived to s3.

        • pigOverrideUrl

          java.lang.String pigOverrideUrl
          An option to override the pig jar from an S3 URL.

        • pigVersion

          java.lang.String pigVersion
          An option to override the pig version on the client side.

        • pigConfigId

          java.lang.String pigConfigId
          An option to override the pig config on the client side.

        • hiveVersion

          java.lang.String hiveVersion
          An option to override the hive version on the client side (for minor versions maybe).

        • hiveConfigId

          java.lang.String hiveConfigId
          An option to override the hive config on the client side.

        • processHandle

          int processHandle
          PID for job - updated by the server.

        • status

          java.lang.String status
          Job status - INIT, RUNNING, SUCCEEDED, KILLED, FAILED (upper case in DB).

        • statusMsg

          java.lang.String statusMsg
          More verbose status message.

        • startTime

          java.lang.Long startTime
          Start time for job - initialized to null.

        • updateTime

          java.lang.Long updateTime
          Last update time for job - initialized to null.

        • finishTime

          java.lang.Long finishTime
          Finish time for job - initialized to zero (for historic reasons).

        • clientHost

          java.lang.String clientHost
          The host/ip address of the client submitting job.

        • hostName

          java.lang.String hostName
          The genie host name on which the job is being run.

        • killURI

          java.lang.String killURI
          REST URI to do a HTTP DEL on to kill this job - points to running instance.

        • outputURI

          java.lang.String outputURI
          URI to fetch the stdout/err and logs.

        • exitCode

          java.lang.Integer exitCode
          Job exit code.

        • forwarded

          boolean forwarded
          Whether this job was forwarded to new instance or not.

        • disableLogArchival

          boolean disableLogArchival
          Whether to disable archive logs or not - default is false.

        • userEmail

          java.lang.String userEmail
          Email address of the user where he expects an email. This is sent once the genie job completes.
